article.description: Evan Boudreaux scored 27 points, grabbed 13 rebounds and Dartmouth cruised to an 87-70 win over Brown on Saturday night.
article.headline: Dartmouth handles Brown 87-70
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Evan Boudreaux scored 27 points, grabbed 13 rebounds and Dartmouth cruised to an 87-70 win over Brown on Saturday night. Taylor Johnson added 22 points for Dartmouth (8-14, 2-6 Ivy League), Miles Wright had 15 and Connor Boehm 11. The Big Green shot 49 percent from the field (32-66) and dominated the glass, 43-21, to snap a five-game skid. Leading by three midway through the first half, Dartmouth broke away with an 11-0 run capped by Boudreaux's jumper to make it 28-14 and took a 38-28 advantage into the break. Brown (7-15, 2-6) trimmed the deficit back to single digits, 47-39, with Cedric Kuakumensah's 3-pointer early in the second half but the Big Green responded with a dunk by Wright and the margin stayed at double figures the rest of the way. Tavon Blackmon led Brown with 22 points, Obi Okolie added 16 and Kuakumensah finished with 15.
